This paper deals with energy-efficient transmission for Cognitive Radio (CR) systems, which involves spectrum sensing and rate allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the efficient transmission and processing of information. The paper also deals with networked systems and communication protocols, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves decision-making and optimization, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper specifically deals with Cognitive Radio (CR) systems, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a low-complexity rate-adaptation policy based on Certainty Equivalent Control, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
